- `unit-tests`: existing `BerremanTests` stays green (`count_at_least` baseline from slice 001's state-of-the-world).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: add `UnitsTests.fs` (AC-D1/AC-D2/AC-A7 round-trips and the `1239.84` relation), `DispersionModelsTests.fs` (AC-D4/AC-D5/AC-D8), `MaterialImportTests.fs` (AC-D3) with the `Si.yml` and `sample-nk.csv` fixtures. The thermo-optic `None`-is-byte-identical and `Some`-applies-correction cases (AC-D8) MUST be asserted.
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block (carry `berreman_unit_tests` from the `unit-tests` capture).

## Risks

- **Medium:** matching `Silicon`/`Langasite` worked closures (`OpticalProperties/Dispersive.fs`) to within 1e-9 (AC-D4) requires the Sellmeier coefficient normalisation (µm² convention) to round-trip exactly through `Units.fs`. Reuse `WaveLength.value` and the `Constants.fs` factors verbatim; do not re-derive any factor.
- **Low:** the `evNmProduct = 1239.84` literal must appear exactly once (D.2); a second copy in any module fails the duplicate-conversion rule (D.11).

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- `Domain/Units.fs` provides the SOLE conversion seam (`toMeters`/`toWaveLength`/`fromMeters`/`wavelengthToUnit`); Part B (slice 003), Part E (slice 005), Part H (slice 008), and Part J (slice 010) MUST call it for every boundary conversion and MUST NOT hand-roll factors.
- `UnitOfMeasure` DU exists; the `defaultUnit` field type is fixed for the per-element hooks Part B (layers) and Part E (sources) place.
- `Domain/DispersionModels.fs` (catalogue + `evaluate`/`toOpticalProperties`, optional `ThermoOptic`, net-new `[<Measure>] K`) and `Domain/MaterialLibrary.fs` (`MaterialEntry`/`MaterialCategory`/`MaterialLibrary`) are available; Part B drag-and-drop (slice 010 J.4) and Part D preview consume `MaterialEntry`. Part I (slice 009) persists the library via the `materialEntry` `$def`.
- `Storage/MaterialImport.fs` produces in-memory `MaterialEntry` values from refractiveindex.info YAML / CSV; Part I (slice 009 §I.8) wraps the shareable-library file format over it.

Per `arc-runner.system-md`, emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML `gates:` block:

```yaml
gates:
  berreman_unit_tests: <int>
```
